To sort an unsorted array of integers using the quicksort algorithm, follow these steps:

1. Choose a pivot element from the array, which can be any integer in the array.
2. Partition the array into two sub-arrays using the pivot element as the boundary element.
3. Recursively sort the left sub-array and the right sub-array using the pivot element as the partition element.
4. Swap the pivot element with the first element in the left sub-array.
5. Return the resultant sorted array.

This algorithm works by repeatedly partitioning the array into smaller and smaller pieces until the entire array is sorted. It uses the idea of a binary tree to recursively sort the left and right sub-arrays. The algorithm is simple and efficient, and can be applied to any array of integer values.

Here is an example of sorting an array using the quicksort algorithm:

```
// C# code to sort an unsorted array of integers using the quicksort algorithm

// Define an array of integers to be sorted
var unsortedArray = new[] { 10, 80, 30, 90, 40, 50, 70 };

// Choose a pivot element from the array (any integer in the array)
var pivot = unsortedArray[0];

// Partition the array using the pivot element as the boundary element
int leftIndex = 0;
int rightIndex = unsortedArray.Length - 1;
while (leftIndex < rightIndex)
{
    // Search for the index of the pivot element in the left sub-array
    while (leftIndex < rightIndex && unsortedArray[leftIndex] < pivot)
        leftIndex++;
    // Search for the index of the pivot element in the right sub-array
    while (leftIndex < rightIndex && unsortedArray[rightIndex] > pivot)
        rightIndex--;
    if (leftIndex < rightIndex)
    {
        // Swap the pivot element with the first element in the left sub-array
        var temp = unsortedArray[leftIndex];
        unsortedArray[leftIndex] = unsortedArray[rightIndex];
        unsortedArray[rightIndex] = temp;
    }
}

// Recursively sort the left and right sub-arrays using the pivot element as the partition element
if (leftIndex < rightIndex)
{
    // Recursively sort the left sub-array
    quickSort(unsortedArray, leftIndex, rightIndex);

    // Swap the pivot element with the first element in the left sub-array
    var temp = unsortedArray[leftIndex];
    unsortedArray[leftIndex] = unsortedArray[rightIndex];
    unsortedArray[rightIndex] = temp;

    // Recursively sort the right sub-array
    quickSort(unsortedArray, leftIndex, rightIndex);
}

// Return the sorted array
return unsortedArray;
